                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <seg type="script">Mediocre, irregular.</seg>
                        <seg type="ink">Black, red (vivid scarlet; the names of the donor in
                           brilliant vermillion).</seg>
                        <date>Late 19th-early 20th cent.</date>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Nomina sacra; names of the donors; doxology (written
                           in alternating red and black letters, e.g., fols. 6r, 7r, 9r, 9v, 10r);
                           several lines or groups of lines on the incipit page of all Texts; a few
                           lines in the incipit of every Miracle in Text II; elements of the
                           punctuation signs; element of Ethiopic numerals.</seg>
                     </handNote>
